</p></sec></sec></body><back><sec><title>Supplementary information</title><p>The online version of this article (10.1038/s41413-019-0055-x) contains supplementary material, which is available to authorized users.</p></sec><ack><title>Acknowledgements</title><p>This work was supported by the Fondazione Telethon Grants GGP09018 and GGP14014, the European Union funded project SYBIL&#x02014;FP7-HEALTH-2013-INNOVATION&#x02014;602300 and by the <italic>Progetti di Rilevante Interesse Nazionale</italic> (PRIN) grant 2015F3JHMB to A.T. A.M. and A.U. were recipients of Marie Curie fellowships from the European Union funded project RUBICON&#x02014;H2020-MSCA-RISE-2015_690850 to A.T. We are indebted with Prof. Paul A. Gleeson, University of Melbourne Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology and Bio21 Molecular Science and Biotechnology Institute, for his advice in the Golgi studies, and with Dr. Rita Di Massimo for editing the paper.</p></ack><notes notes-type="author-contribution"><title>Author contributions</title><p>A.M. designed, performed, and evaluated the work that led to the submission, acquired data, and played an important role in interpreting the results; M.C. contributed to study design, supervised the work, and played an important role in interpreting the results; A.C., R.P., A.U., J.A.C., and HO performed the work and acquired data; S.L. and J.B. trained the RUBICON fellows (A.M. and A.U.) in ER stress and vesicular trafficking experiments. N.R. contributed to the experimental design and played an important role in interpreting the results. A.T. coordinated the study, played an important role in interpreting the results, and wrote the paper. All authors revised and approved the final version of the paper.</p></notes><notes notes-type="COI-statement"><title>Competing interests</title><p id="Par41">A.T., N.R., M.C., and A.M. are co-inventors of the patented siRNA treatment for the ADO2 therapy used in this article. The remaining authors declare no competing interests.</p></notes><ref-list id="Bib1"><title>References</title><ref id="CR1"><label>1.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Teti</surname><given-names>A</given-names></name><name><surname>Econs</surname><given-names>MJ</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Osteopetroses, emphasizing potential approaches to treatment</article-title><source>Bone</source><year>2017</year><volume>102</volume><fpage>50</fpage><lpage>59</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1016/j.bone.2017.02.002</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">28167345</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="CR2"><label>2.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Albers-Sch&#x000f6;nberg</surname><given-names>H</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>R&#x000f6;ntgenbilder einer seltenen Knock-enerkrankung</article-title><source>Munch. Med. Wochenscher</source><year>1904</year><volume>5</volume><fpage>365</fpage><lpage>368</lpage></element-citation></ref><ref id="CR3"><label>3.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Hill</surname><given-names>BG</given-names></name><name><surname>Charlton</surname><given-names>WS</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Albers-Schonberg disease</article-title><source>Med. J. Aust.</source><year>1965</year><volume>2</volume><fpage>365</fpage><lpage>367</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">5889798</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="CR4"><label>4.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Waguespack</surname><given-names>SG</given-names></name><name><surname>Hui</surname><given-names>SL</given-names></name><name><surname>DiMeglio</surname><given-names>LA</given-names></name><name><surname>Econs</surname><given-names>MJ</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Autosomal do